               <p>WILLIAM THORP, JUN. I am son of William Thorp; he is a <rs id="t18280703-105-viclabel534" type="occupation">stable-keeper</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280703-105-victim678 t18280703-105-viclabel534"></join>. I saw the prisoner with a pair of spurs of mine on, which led me to go to his lodging, where I found these articles; he was charged with stealing them, but he said nothing - I have worn this coat from the time it was new; I know these spurs, from having worn them some months - they were found at the pawnbroker's; I was in the habit of using these articles - the prisoner had been with us about six months.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280703-105-person679">
